§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A function $f: 𝗥^n → 𝗥$ is called a ❬functional❭. ⦉

  ‖ If $f$ is linear, then $f(x) = a^⊤ x$ for all $x$. ⦉

  ‖ So every vector $a ∈ 𝗥^n$ can be thought to correspond to
    a linear functional. ⦉
